Draco shrugged and began to occlude. “Perhaps if you hadn’t allowed a sociopath to brand
me for the cause I would still believe in it.”
“Draco!” said his mother in a scandalized voice.
“What?” he asked, now turning his dull stare to look at her instead. “Why is that so
surprising to you?”
“The war changed you, I’ll admit that,” said Narcissa slowly. “But it made you grow up. It
