“Pansy!” cried Narcissa, leaping to her feet and running to the witch.
“My apologies, Narcissa,” said Pansy a bit faintly. “I’m not feeling my best.”
Pansy’s distraction successfully halted the conversation with Draco’s parents. Everyone
converged on her, and as Narcissa was calling one of the elves to bring water and some food,
