She was pointing that out.”
There was an uncomfortable silence at this.
“Draco…” said Theo quietly.
Draco turned to look at him.
“Was she telling the truth? About being tortured in the drawing room, I mean?”
Draco went cold, and he could tell his friends saw his expression change.
“It was Bellatrix,” he said quietly. “She was dead after the war, so Granger never really
spoke up about it until today. There aren’t many who know the details.”
“And you all watched?” prodded Blaise carefully.
Draco just nodded. “My parents asked me to identify her and the others, and I delayed a little
bit… but I couldn’t do anything to help once Bella arrived. She recognized Granger
