“You don’t have a conjugal visit on the books tonight,” said Maywood conversationally.
“No, Sir,” said Draco. “I am requesting a spontaneous visit. All four of us at the same time.”
Maywood eyed them. “The visitor policy…” he started.
“Allows up to five visitors at once,” said Draco. “At any time of the day. It was part of the
Azkaban Reform Act of 2001.”
A ghost of a smile crossed Maywood’s face. “Right you are. So silly of me. I’ll go see if
Miss Granger is willing to see you.”
Draco nodded and started to pace as he waited for Maywood to return.
“Merlin, Draco, sit down,” said Pansy.
“Can’t,” he muttered. “What if she says no? What if she declines? What if –”
“She won’t,” insisted Pansy. “Just breathe.”
