splashes from the other side of the door.
She’s in there naked. She’s ready for you. Take her.
Draco groaned and in a fit of desperation grabbed the black stick and pointed it to the TV,
pushing the same buttons Granger had taught him. He flipped through various channels, until
he landed on something he couldn’t help but watch.
Beauty and the Beast.
He selected it and watched in slight disbelief as a French brunette named Belle began to sing
a song about wanting to escape her boring life. Evidently the villagers considered her odd
because she liked to read. And before long, a tall, dark and strapping man was trying to
garner her attention.
He’s supposed to represent Weasley? Ha!
Not only was the hair color entirely wrong, but this Gaston fellow seemed far more confident
than Weasley had ever been. Draco scowled as he tried to woo Belle, who – much to Draco’s
